official_text:
a. Define and document the types of accounts allowed and specifically prohibited for use within the system;
b. Assign account managers;
c. Require organization-defined prerequisites and criteria for group and role membership;
d. Specify:
  1. Authorized users of the system;
  2. Group and role membership; and
  3. Access authorizations (i.e., privileges) and organization-defined attributes (as required) for each account;
e. Require approvals by organization-defined personnel or roles for requests to create accounts;
f. Create, enable, modify, disable, and remove accounts in accordance with organization-defined policy, procedures, prerequisites, and criteria;
g. Monitor the use of accounts;
h. Notify account managers and organization-defined personnel or roles within:
  1. organization-defined time period when accounts are no longer required;
  2. organization-defined time period when users are terminated or transferred; and
  3. organization-defined time period when system usage or need-to-know changes for an individual;
i. Authorize access to the system based on:
  1. A valid access authorization;
  2. Intended system usage; and
  3. organization-defined attributes (as required);
j. Review accounts for compliance with account management requirements organization-defined frequency;
k. Establish and implement a process for changing shared or group account authenticators (if deployed) when individuals are removed from the group; and
l. Align account management processes with personnel termination and transfer processes.

enhancements.official_text:
(a) Establish and administer privileged user accounts in accordance with [Assignment: organization-defined role-based access scheme; organization-defined attribute-based access scheme];
(b) Monitor privileged role or attribute assignments;
(c) Monitor changes to roles or attributes; and
(d) Revoke access when privileged role or attribute assignments are no longer appropriate.

fixed_content.official_text:
Enforce organization-defined discretionary access control policy over the set of covered subjects and objects specified in the policy, and where the policy specifies that a subject that has been granted access to information can do one or more of the following:
(a) Pass the information to other subjects or objects;
(b) Grant its privileges to other subjects;
(c) Change security attributes on subjects, objects, the system, or the system components;
(d) Choose the security attributes to be associated with newly created or revised objects; or
(e) Change the rules governing access control.

official_text:
a. Display [Assignment: organization-defined system use notification message or banner] to users before granting access to the system that provides privacy and security notices consistent with applicable laws, Executive Orders, directives, regulations, policies, standards, and guidelines and state that: (1) Users are accessing a U.S. Government system; (2) System usage may be monitored, recorded, and subject to audit; (3) Unauthorized use of the system is prohibited and subject to criminal and civil penalties; and (4) Use of the system indicates consent to monitoring and recording;
b. Retain the notification message or banner on the screen until users acknowledge the usage conditions and take explicit actions to log on to or further access the system; and
c. For publicly accessible systems: (1) Display system use information [Assignment: organization-defined conditions], before granting further access to the publicly accessible system; (2) Display references, if any, to monitoring, recording, or auditing that are consistent with privacy accommodations for such systems that generally prohibit those activities; and (3) Include a description of the authorized uses of the system.

windows.powershell:
# AC-14: Permitted Actions Without Identification or Authentication
# Purpose: Verify guest accounts are disabled on Windows systems

Write-Host "=== AC-14 Compliance Check (Windows) ===" -ForegroundColor Cyan
Write-Host ""

# Check Guest Account Status
Write-Host "[CHECK] Guest Account Status" -ForegroundColor Yellow
$GuestAccount = Get-LocalUser -Name "Guest" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
if ($GuestAccount) {
    if ($GuestAccount.Enabled) {
        Write-Host "  [FAIL] Guest account is ENABLED" -ForegroundColor Red
        Write-Host "  ACTION: Disable with 'Disable-LocalUser -Name Guest'" -ForegroundColor Red
    } else {
        Write-Host "  [PASS] Guest account is disabled" -ForegroundColor Green
    }
} else {
    Write-Host "  [INFO] Guest account not found" -ForegroundColor Gray
}
Write-Host ""

# Check Anonymous Logon Restrictions
Write-Host "[CHECK] Anonymous Logon Security Policy" -ForegroundColor Yellow
$SecPolicy = secedit /export /cfg "$env:TEMP\secpol.cfg" 2>&1
$AnonSID = Select-String -Path "$env:TEMP\secpol.cfg" -Pattern "SeNetworkLogonRight" | Select-String "S-1-5-7"
if ($AnonSID) {
    Write-Host "  [WARN] Anonymous SID has network logon rights" -ForegroundColor Yellow
    Write-Host "  ACTION: Review and restrict via Local Security Policy" -ForegroundColor Yellow
} else {
    Write-Host "  [PASS] Anonymous logon appears restricted" -ForegroundColor Green
}
Remove-Item "$env:TEMP\secpol.cfg" -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
Write-Host ""

Write-Host "=== AC-14 POLICY REMINDER ===" -ForegroundColor Cyan
Write-Host "Document all permitted unauthenticated actions in the security plan."
Write-Host "If no actions are permitted, document assignment value as 'None'."
Write-Host ""

# AC-18(1) Authentication and Encryption for Windows
# Validate wireless profiles use strong authentication and encryption

Write-Host "Checking wireless profile security settings..."

$profiles = netsh wlan show profiles | Select-String 'All User Profile' | ForEach-Object { ($_ -split ':')[1].Trim() }

foreach ($profile in $profiles) {
    Write-Host "\nProfile: $profile"
    $details = netsh wlan show profile name="$profile" key=clear

    # Check authentication
    $auth = $details | Select-String 'Authentication'
    Write-Host "$auth"

    # Check encryption
    $cipher = $details | Select-String 'Cipher'
    Write-Host "$cipher"

    # Validate security
    if ($details -match 'WPA3|WPA2' -and $details -match 'AES|CCMP') {
        Write-Host "[PASS] Strong authentication and encryption" -ForegroundColor Green
    } elseif ($details -match 'WPA' -and $details -match 'TKIP') {
        Write-Host "[WARN] Weak encryption (TKIP) - upgrade to WPA2/WPA3 with AES" -ForegroundColor Yellow
    } elseif ($details -match 'WEP|Open') {
        Write-Host "[FAIL] Insecure encryption - MUST upgrade" -ForegroundColor Red
    }
}

# AC-18(3) Disable Wireless Networking for Windows
# Requires Administrator privileges

if (-not ([Security.Principal.WindowsPrincipal][Security.Principal.WindowsIdentity]::GetCurrent()).IsInRole([Security.Principal.WindowsBuiltInRole]::Administrator)) {
    Write-Error "This script must be run as Administrator"
    exit 1
}

Write-Host "[AC-18(3)] Disabling wireless networking capabilities..." -ForegroundColor Cyan

# Disable WiFi adapters
Write-Host "`nDisabling WiFi adapters..."
$wifiAdapters = Get-NetAdapter | Where-Object { $_.InterfaceDescription -match 'Wireless|Wi-Fi|802.11' -and $_.Status -ne 'Disabled' }
if ($wifiAdapters) {
    foreach ($adapter in $wifiAdapters) {
        Write-Host "  Disabling: $($adapter.Name) - $($adapter.InterfaceDescription)"
        Disable-NetAdapter -Name $adapter.Name -Confirm:$false
    }
    Write-Host "  [SUCCESS] WiFi adapters disabled" -ForegroundColor Green
} else {
    Write-Host "  No active WiFi adapters found" -ForegroundColor Gray
}

# Disable Bluetooth adapters
Write-Host "`nDisabling Bluetooth adapters..."
$bluetoothDevices = Get-PnpDevice -Class Bluetooth | Where-Object { $_.Status -eq 'OK' }
if ($bluetoothDevices) {
    foreach ($device in $bluetoothDevices) {
        Write-Host "  Disabling: $($device.FriendlyName)"
        Disable-PnpDevice -InstanceId $device.InstanceId -Confirm:$false
    }
    Write-Host "  [SUCCESS] Bluetooth adapters disabled" -ForegroundColor Green
} else {
    Write-Host "  No active Bluetooth adapters found" -ForegroundColor Gray
}

# Stop and disable wireless services
Write-Host "`nDisabling wireless services..."
$wirelessServices = @('WlanSvc', 'bthserv')
foreach ($service in $wirelessServices) {
    $svc = Get-Service -Name $service -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
    if ($svc) {
        Write-Host "  Stopping and disabling: $($svc.DisplayName)"
        Stop-Service -Name $service -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
        Set-Service -Name $service -StartupType Disabled
    }
}

# Use Group Policy to prevent wireless re-enabling (requires GPO)
Write-Host "`nConfiguring Group Policy..."
Write-Host "  Note: Use Group Policy Editor (gpedit.msc) to enforce:"
Write-Host "    Computer Config > Admin Templates > Network > Windows Connect Now"
Write-Host "    - Prohibit access to Windows Connect Now wizards: Enabled"
Write-Host "    Computer Config > Admin Templates > Network > WLAN Service"
Write-Host "    - Allow Windows to automatically connect to suggested open hotspots: Disabled"

Write-Host "`n[SUCCESS] Wireless networking capabilities disabled." -ForegroundColor Green
Write-Host "Recommendation: Configure BIOS/UEFI to disable wireless hardware for additional protection." -ForegroundColor Yellow

# Verification
Write-Host "`nVerification:"
Get-NetAdapter | Where-Object { $_.InterfaceDescription -match 'Wireless|Wi-Fi|Bluetooth' } | Format-Table Name, InterfaceDescription, Status -AutoSize

windows.audit:
$ErrorActionPreference = 'SilentlyContinue'
Write-Host 'Checking Mobile Device Management (MDM) enrollment...'
$mdmEnrolled = Get-WmiObject -Namespace root\cimv2\mdm\dmmap -Class MDM_EnterpriseModernAppManagement_AppManagement01
if ($mdmEnrolled) {
    Write-Host 'PASS: System is MDM enrolled'
} else {
    Write-Host 'FAIL: System is not MDM enrolled'
}

Write-Host 'Checking BitLocker encryption (related to AC-19(5))...'
$bitlockerStatus = Get-BitLockerVolume -MountPoint C:
if ($bitlockerStatus.ProtectionStatus -eq 'On') {
    Write-Host 'PASS: BitLocker is enabled on system drive'
} else {
    Write-Host 'WARNING: BitLocker is not enabled (required for AC-19(5))'
}

Write-Host 'Checking VPN client installation...'
$vpnConnections = Get-VpnConnection
if ($vpnConnections) {
    Write-Host 'PASS: VPN connections configured'
} else {
    Write-Host 'WARNING: No VPN connections found'
}

Write-Host 'Checking Windows Defender status...'
$defenderStatus = Get-MpComputerStatus
if ($defenderStatus.AntivirusEnabled) {
    Write-Host 'PASS: Antivirus is enabled'
} else {
    Write-Host 'FAIL: Antivirus is not enabled'
}

$ErrorActionPreference = 'SilentlyContinue'
Write-Host 'AC-19(1): Checking portable storage device controls...'

# Check if removable storage is restricted via Group Policy
$regPath = 'HKLM:\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\RemovableStorageDevices'
if (Test-Path $regPath) {
    $denyRead = Get-ItemProperty -Path "$regPath\{53f5630d-b6bf-11d0-94f2-00a0c91efb8b}" -Name 'Deny_Read' -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
    $denyWrite = Get-ItemProperty -Path "$regPath\{53f5630d-b6bf-11d0-94f2-00a0c91efb8b}" -Name 'Deny_Write' -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue

    if ($denyWrite.Deny_Write -eq 1) {
        Write-Host 'PASS: Removable storage write access is denied by policy'
    } else {
        Write-Host 'FAIL: Removable storage write access is not restricted'
    }

    if ($denyRead.Deny_Read -eq 1) {
        Write-Host 'INFO: Removable storage read access is denied by policy (very restrictive)'
    } else {
        Write-Host 'INFO: Removable storage read access is allowed'
    }
} else {
    Write-Host 'FAIL: Removable storage device policies not configured'
}

# Check BitLocker To Go (encryption for removable storage)
$bitlockerReg = 'HKLM:\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\FVE'
if (Test-Path $bitlockerReg) {
    $rdvRequired = Get-ItemProperty -Path $bitlockerReg -Name 'RDVDenyWriteAccess' -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
    if ($rdvRequired.RDVDenyWriteAccess -eq 1) {
        Write-Host 'PASS: BitLocker To Go encryption required for removable drives'
    } else {
        Write-Host 'INFO: BitLocker To Go not enforced for removable drives'
    }
} else {
    Write-Host 'INFO: BitLocker To Go policies not configured'
}

# List currently connected removable storage devices
Write-Host ''
Write-Host 'Currently connected removable storage devices:'
Get-PnpDevice -Class 'USB','DiskDrive' | Where-Object {$_.Status -eq 'OK'} | Format-Table -AutoSize

$ErrorActionPreference = 'SilentlyContinue'
Write-Host 'AC-19(2): Checking organizational portable storage restrictions...'

# Check if BitLocker To Go is enforced
$regPath = 'HKLM:\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\FVE'
if (Test-Path $regPath) {
    $rdvEncryption = Get-ItemProperty -Path $regPath -Name 'RDVDenyWriteAccess' -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue

    if ($rdvEncryption.RDVDenyWriteAccess -eq 1) {
        Write-Host 'PASS: BitLocker To Go encryption is required for removable drives'
    } else {
        Write-Host 'FAIL: BitLocker To Go encryption is not enforced'
    }
} else {
    Write-Host 'FAIL: BitLocker To Go policies not configured'
}

# Check for Windows Defender
$defenderStatus = Get-MpComputerStatus
if ($defenderStatus.AntivirusEnabled) {
    Write-Host 'PASS: Windows Defender is enabled (can scan portable storage)'

    if ($defenderStatus.AntivirusSignatureLastUpdated -gt (Get-Date).AddDays(-7)) {
        Write-Host 'PASS: Antivirus definitions are up to date'
    } else {
        Write-Host 'WARNING: Antivirus definitions may be outdated'
    }
} else {
    Write-Host 'FAIL: Windows Defender is not enabled'
}

# List BitLocker encrypted removable drives
Write-Host ''
Write-Host 'BitLocker encrypted removable drives:'
Get-BitLockerVolume | Where-Object {$_.VolumeType -eq 'Data'} | Format-Table MountPoint, EncryptionMethod, ProtectionStatus -AutoSize

$ErrorActionPreference = 'SilentlyContinue'
Write-Host 'AC-19(3): Checking system classification and portable storage restrictions...'

# Check for system classification (custom implementation via registry)
$classificationReg = 'HKLM:\SOFTWARE\Organization\SystemClassification'
if (Test-Path $classificationReg) {
    $classification = Get-ItemProperty -Path $classificationReg -Name 'Level' -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
    if ($classification) {
        Write-Host "PASS: System classification is defined: $($classification.Level)"
    } else {
        Write-Host 'WARNING: System classification registry key exists but Level not set'
    }
} else {
    Write-Host 'WARNING: System classification not defined'
    Write-Host 'Recommended: Create registry key HKLM:\SOFTWARE\Organization\SystemClassification'
    Write-Host 'Set Level value to: HIGH, MODERATE, or LOW'
}

# Check removable storage policy
$regPath = 'HKLM:\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\RemovableStorageDevices'
if (Test-Path $regPath) {
    $usbStorageGUID = '{53f5630d-b6bf-11d0-94f2-00a0c91efb8b}'
    $fullPath = "$regPath\$usbStorageGUID"

    $denyWrite = Get-ItemProperty -Path $fullPath -Name 'Deny_Write' -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
    $denyRead = Get-ItemProperty -Path $fullPath -Name 'Deny_Read' -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue

    if ($denyWrite.Deny_Write -eq 1) {
        Write-Host 'PASS: Removable storage write access is restricted'
    } else {
        Write-Host 'INFO: Removable storage write access is not restricted'
    }

    if ($denyRead.Deny_Read -eq 1) {
        Write-Host 'PASS: Removable storage read access is restricted (HIGH security)'
    } else {
        Write-Host 'INFO: Removable storage read access is allowed'
    }
} else {
    Write-Host 'INFO: Removable storage device policies not configured'
}

Write-Host ''
Write-Host 'Classification-based recommendations:'
Write-Host 'HIGH: Deny both read and write to all removable storage'
Write-Host 'MODERATE: Deny write, allow read (or require BitLocker To Go)'
Write-Host 'LOW: Monitor-only with audit logging'

windows.remediation:
$ErrorActionPreference = 'Stop'
Write-Host 'Implementing AC-19(3): Classification-based portable storage restrictions...'

# Prompt for system classification if not defined
$classificationReg = 'HKLM:\SOFTWARE\Organization\SystemClassification'
if (-not (Test-Path $classificationReg)) {
    New-Item -Path 'HKLM:\SOFTWARE\Organization' -Force | Out-Null
    New-Item -Path $classificationReg -Force | Out-Null
}

$existingClassification = Get-ItemProperty -Path $classificationReg -Name 'Level' -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
if (-not $existingClassification) {
    Write-Host 'System classification not defined.'
    Write-Host 'Enter system classification (HIGH/MODERATE/LOW):'
    $classification = Read-Host
    Set-ItemProperty -Path $classificationReg -Name 'Level' -Value $classification
    Write-Host "System classified as: $classification"
} else {
    $classification = $existingClassification.Level
    Write-Host "Existing classification: $classification"
}

# Configure removable storage policies based on classification
$regPath = 'HKLM:\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\RemovableStorageDevices'
$usbStorageGUID = '{53f5630d-b6bf-11d0-94f2-00a0c91efb8b}'
$fullPath = "$regPath\$usbStorageGUID"

if (-not (Test-Path $regPath)) {
    New-Item -Path $regPath -Force | Out-Null
}
if (-not (Test-Path $fullPath)) {
    New-Item -Path $fullPath -Force | Out-Null
}

switch ($classification.ToUpper()) {
    'HIGH' {
        Write-Host 'Configuring STRICT policy for HIGH classification...'
        Set-ItemProperty -Path $fullPath -Name 'Deny_Write' -Value 1 -Type DWord
        Set-ItemProperty -Path $fullPath -Name 'Deny_Read' -Value 1 -Type DWord
        Write-Host 'HIGH: Both read and write access to removable storage DENIED'
    }
    'MODERATE' {
        Write-Host 'Configuring MODERATE policy for MODERATE classification...'
        Set-ItemProperty -Path $fullPath -Name 'Deny_Write' -Value 1 -Type DWord
        Set-ItemProperty -Path $fullPath -Name 'Deny_Read' -Value 0 -Type DWord

        # Require BitLocker To Go
        $bitlockerReg = 'HKLM:\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\FVE'
        if (-not (Test-Path $bitlockerReg)) {
            New-Item -Path $bitlockerReg -Force | Out-Null
        }
        Set-ItemProperty -Path $bitlockerReg -Name 'RDVDenyWriteAccess' -Value 1 -Type DWord

        Write-Host 'MODERATE: Write access denied, read allowed, BitLocker To Go required'
    }
    'LOW' {
        Write-Host 'Configuring PERMISSIVE policy for LOW classification...'
        Set-ItemProperty -Path $fullPath -Name 'Deny_Write' -Value 0 -Type DWord
        Set-ItemProperty -Path $fullPath -Name 'Deny_Read' -Value 0 -Type DWord
        Write-Host 'LOW: Read and write allowed (monitor-only mode)'
        Write-Host 'Configure audit logging separately for monitoring'
    }
    default {
        Write-Host 'ERROR: Invalid classification. Must be HIGH, MODERATE, or LOW'
        exit 1
    }
}

Write-Host ''
Write-Host 'AC-19(3) implementation complete.'
Write-Host "System classification: $classification"
Write-Host 'Policy enforced per classification level.'
Write-Host 'Run "gpupdate /force" to apply Group Policy changes immediately.'

windows.audit:
$ErrorActionPreference = 'SilentlyContinue'
Write-Host 'AC-19(4): Checking mobile device restrictions for classified facilities...'
Write-Host 'NOTE: This is primarily an organizational/physical security control.'
Write-Host ''

# Check WiFi status
Write-Host 'Checking wireless hardware status...'
$wifiAdapters = Get-NetAdapter | Where-Object {$_.InterfaceDescription -like '*wireless*' -or $_.InterfaceDescription -like '*Wi-Fi*'}
if ($wifiAdapters) {
    $enabledWifi = $wifiAdapters | Where-Object {$_.Status -eq 'Up'}
    if ($enabledWifi) {
        Write-Host 'WARNING: WiFi adapter(s) are enabled (should be disabled in classified facility)'
        $enabledWifi | Format-Table Name, Status, InterfaceDescription
    } else {
        Write-Host 'PASS: WiFi adapters are disabled'
    }
} else {
    Write-Host 'PASS: No WiFi adapters detected'
}

# Check Bluetooth status
$bluetoothDevices = Get-PnpDevice -Class 'Bluetooth' | Where-Object {$_.Status -eq 'OK'}
if ($bluetoothDevices) {
    Write-Host 'WARNING: Bluetooth devices detected and enabled'
    $bluetoothDevices | Format-Table FriendlyName, Status
} else {
    Write-Host 'PASS: No active Bluetooth devices detected'
}

# Check for camera devices
$cameraDevices = Get-PnpDevice -Class 'Camera','Image' | Where-Object {$_.Status -eq 'OK'}
if ($cameraDevices) {
    Write-Host "WARNING: $($cameraDevices.Count) camera device(s) detected"
    $cameraDevices | Format-Table FriendlyName, Status
} else {
    Write-Host 'PASS: No camera devices detected'
}

# Check for audio recording devices
$audioDevices = Get-PnpDevice -Class 'AudioEndpoint','Media' | Where-Object {$_.FriendlyName -like '*microphone*'}
if ($audioDevices) {
    Write-Host "INFO: $($audioDevices.Count) microphone device(s) detected"
}

Write-Host ''
Write-Host 'IMPORTANT: AC-19(4) requires organizational controls:'
Write-Host '- Mobile device prohibition policy for classified facilities'
Write-Host '- Physical security controls (lockers, RF detection, guards)'
Write-Host '- Exception process for specifically authorized devices'
Write-Host '- Regular security inspections and audits'
Write-Host '- Disciplinary measures for policy violations'

windows.remediation:
$ErrorActionPreference = 'Stop'
Write-Host 'Implementing AC-19(4): Classified facility mobile device restrictions...'
Write-Host 'WARNING: This will disable wireless hardware on this system.'
Write-Host ''

$confirm = Read-Host 'Is this system authorized for classified facility use? (yes/no)'
if ($confirm -ne 'yes') {
    Write-Host 'Aborted. This script should only be run on authorized systems.'
    exit 1
}

Write-Host 'Disabling wireless hardware...'

# Disable all WiFi adapters
$wifiAdapters = Get-NetAdapter | Where-Object {$_.InterfaceDescription -like '*wireless*' -or $_.InterfaceDescription -like '*Wi-Fi*'}
if ($wifiAdapters) {
    foreach ($adapter in $wifiAdapters) {
        Disable-NetAdapter -Name $adapter.Name -Confirm:$false
        Write-Host "Disabled WiFi adapter: $($adapter.Name)"
    }
} else {
    Write-Host 'No WiFi adapters found'
}

# Disable Bluetooth devices
$bluetoothDevices = Get-PnpDevice -Class 'Bluetooth' | Where-Object {$_.Status -eq 'OK'}
if ($bluetoothDevices) {
    foreach ($device in $bluetoothDevices) {
        Disable-PnpDevice -InstanceId $device.InstanceId -Confirm:$false
        Write-Host "Disabled Bluetooth: $($device.FriendlyName)"
    }
} else {
    Write-Host 'No Bluetooth devices found'
}

# Disable camera devices (optional - may affect legitimate video conferencing)
$confirmCamera = Read-Host 'Disable camera devices? (yes/no)'
if ($confirmCamera -eq 'yes') {
    $cameraDevices = Get-PnpDevice -Class 'Camera','Image' | Where-Object {$_.Status -eq 'OK'}
    if ($cameraDevices) {
        foreach ($camera in $cameraDevices) {
            Disable-PnpDevice -InstanceId $camera.InstanceId -Confirm:$false
            Write-Host "Disabled camera: $($camera.FriendlyName)"
        }
    }
}

# Create Group Policy to prevent re-enabling wireless
$regPath = 'HKLM:\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\NetworkConnectivityStatusIndicator'
if (-not (Test-Path $regPath)) {
    New-Item -Path $regPath -Force | Out-Null
}
Set-ItemProperty -Path $regPath -Name 'NoActiveProbe' -Value 1 -Type DWord

Write-Host ''
Write-Host 'AC-19(4) technical implementation complete.'
Write-Host ''
Write-Host 'REMAINING ORGANIZATIONAL REQUIREMENTS:'
Write-Host '1. Physical camera/microphone removal (if hardware present)'
Write-Host '2. Apply tamper-evident seals to device'
Write-Host '3. Register device in authorized device inventory'
Write-Host '4. Schedule regular security inspections'
Write-Host '5. Train user on classified facility restrictions'
Write-Host '6. Document authorization and restrictions'
Write-Host ''
Write-Host 'REBOOT RECOMMENDED to ensure all hardware is fully disabled.'

windows.audit:
$ErrorActionPreference = 'SilentlyContinue'
Write-Host 'AC-19(5): Checking mobile device encryption...'
Write-Host ''

# Check BitLocker status on all drives
Write-Host 'Checking BitLocker encryption status...'
$allVolumes = Get-BitLockerVolume

if ($allVolumes) {
    foreach ($volume in $allVolumes) {
        Write-Host "Drive: $($volume.MountPoint)"
        Write-Host "  Volume Status: $($volume.VolumeStatus)"
        Write-Host "  Protection Status: $($volume.ProtectionStatus)"
        Write-Host "  Encryption Method: $($volume.EncryptionMethod)"
        Write-Host "  Encryption Percentage: $($volume.EncryptionPercentage)%"

        if ($volume.MountPoint -eq 'C:' -and $volume.ProtectionStatus -eq 'On') {
            Write-Host '  PASS: System drive (C:) is BitLocker encrypted'
        } elseif ($volume.MountPoint -eq 'C:') {
            Write-Host '  FAIL: System drive (C:) is NOT encrypted (REQUIRED for AC-19(5))'
        }

        # Check encryption method strength
        if ($volume.EncryptionMethod -like '*Aes256*' -or $volume.EncryptionMethod -like '*XtsAes256*') {
            Write-Host '  PASS: Using AES-256 encryption (strong)'
        } elseif ($volume.EncryptionMethod -like '*Aes128*' -or $volume.EncryptionMethod -like '*XtsAes128*') {
            Write-Host '  WARNING: Using AES-128 (acceptable but AES-256 preferred)'
        } elseif ($volume.ProtectionStatus -eq 'On') {
            Write-Host '  WARNING: Encryption method may be weak'
        }

        Write-Host ''
    }
} else {
    Write-Host 'FAIL: Unable to query BitLocker status (BitLocker may not be available)'
}

# Check TPM status
Write-Host 'Checking TPM (Trusted Platform Module) status...'
$tpm = Get-Tpm
if ($tpm.TpmPresent) {
    Write-Host 'PASS: TPM is present'
    if ($tpm.TpmReady) {
        Write-Host 'PASS: TPM is ready for BitLocker'
    } else {
        Write-Host 'WARNING: TPM is present but not ready (may need initialization)'
    }
    if ($tpm.TpmEnabled) {
        Write-Host 'PASS: TPM is enabled'
    } else {
        Write-Host 'WARNING: TPM is disabled'
    }
} else {
    Write-Host 'WARNING: TPM not present (BitLocker can use password-only, less secure)'
}

Write-Host ''
Write-Host 'RECOMMENDATION: For AC-19(5) compliance (Moderate/High baselines):'
Write-Host '- Enable BitLocker on all fixed drives with AES-256'
Write-Host '- Use TPM + PIN for system drive protection'
Write-Host '- Escrow recovery keys to Active Directory or secure backup'
Write-Host '- For removable drives: Use BitLocker To Go'

official_text:
a. Designate individuals authorized to make information publicly accessible;

b. Train authorized individuals to ensure that publicly accessible information does not contain nonpublic information;

c. Review the proposed content of information prior to posting onto the publicly accessible system to ensure that nonpublic information is not included; and

d. Review the content on the publicly accessible system for nonpublic information [Assignment: organization-defined frequency] and remove such information, if discovered.
